Connecting to a Cluster
Cache with Redis provides access to a cluster over a private endpoint.

With private endpoints (https://docs.oracle.com/iaas/Content/Network/Concepts/privateaccess.htm#private-endpoints), traffic doesn't go over the internet. You can only connect to the cluster from a client within the same VCN as the cluster or another VCN with appropriate gateways and route rules configured.

Ways to connect to a cluster:

Redis CLI version 7 is recommended, see Connecting with the Redis CLI.https://docs.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/Content/redis/connecttorediscluster.htm#connecttorediscluster__connectrediscli
Using GUI such as RedisInsight or Redis Commander
Deploying RedisInsight GUI on OCI with Container Instances
This guide will walk you through deploying RedisInsight on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) using Container Instances.

For detailed instructions on creating container instances on OCI, refer to the Container Instances documentation.https://docs.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/Content/container-instances/creating-a-container-instance.htm

Step-by-Step Guide
1. Create a Container Instance
First, you need to create a container instance on OCI. When setting this up, ensure that you place the container instance in the same Virtual Cloud Network (VCN) and private subnet where your Redis cluster is running. This setup will allow seamless communication between RedisInsight and your Redis cluster.

2. Configure the RedisInsight Container
Next, configure the RedisInsight container with the following settings:

External Registry
Registry hostname: docker.io
Repository: redis/redisinsight
Tag: latest
3. Adjust Security Settings
To access the RedisInsight GUI, you need to add a rule to your VCN security list to allow traffic on port 5540. This rule is crucial for enabling external access to the RedisInsight interface.

4. Access the RedisInsight GUI
Once your container instance is created and running, you can access the RedisInsight GUI through your web browser.

Use the following URL format, replacing <container instance IP> with the actual IP address of your container instance:

http://<container instance IP>:5540/



5. Connect to Your Redis Database
In the RedisInsight GUI, you can add a new Redis database. Use the Primary endpoint URL of your Redis cluster. Additionally, make sure to check the "Use TLS" checkbox to ensure a secure connection.

By following these steps, you'll have a fully functional RedisInsight GUI running on OCI, providing you with an intuitive interface to manage and monitor your Redis databases effectively.





